OL,5,Cfunding
OL,7,FA survey of 1,000 disabled people by
OL,8,Fthe national disability charity SENSE
OL,9,Ffound that nearly a quarter fear they
OL,10,Fwill no longer be able to afford
OL,11,Fessentials like energy and food if the
OL,12,Fwelfare reforms are voted in.
OL,14,F2 in 5 fear they'll struggle to cope
OL,15,Ffinancially if the changes go ahead.
OL,17,FOne in five warned that losing this
OL,18,Fsupport would lead them to depend more
OL,19,Fheavily on the NHS.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G5/10
