OL,7,FSteven Morris, from SENSE, said: "The
OL,8,FPIP is there to support with the
OL,9,Fadditional costs of being disabled.
OL,11,F"It may be she needs more electricity
OL,12,Fto power a ventilator or charge
OL,13,Fwheelchairs. These changes, these
OL,14,Fadditional costs are not going to
OL,15,Fdisappear when somebody loses their
OL,16,FPIP. Instead, it's going to push more
OL,17,Fpeople into poverty."
OL,19,FHow PIP works and what's changing
